data.message: Its hard to appreciate any other rapper when you already know Eminem is better in every aspect of it

replies.message: Sounds more like you're unwilling to look for other artists and broaden your hiphip library.. that's okay though, just sad that you'll only ever be listening to Eminem while he's incredible but by far not the best in every aspect.

TUPAC is legendary for his passion in his voice and lyrics and for how he made u feel what he was saying...Em said it exactly right..Tupac was definitely one of the best ever if not the best...And as far as lyrical talent..Biggie is hard to beat.Dude could go in the studio and freestyle a whole album and sell millions. He was able to flow to the beat like nobody has ever done before or since and that fat bastard was smooth with it and hard as hell when he wanted to be.He was a great story teller in his rhymes, complete with characters and all.Remember ,"darkskin Jamaine" lol..Now Em is a genius with lyrics and has an extisive vocabulary and able to bend words to make it rhyme even when it doesnt even rhyme. He spits venom with his lyrics and is a wordsmith and can mix match words and put them together better than any rapper ever has...He is truly a mad scientist of rap and can flo any style so he is also unique in that way.Plus he is a great producer..They r all three great in their own.way...I can also appreciate other rappers like Jay-Z, Royce 5'9 is really dope, Jada,Rahkim, Talib Qwali, NAS,DMX, Yelawolf, Joe Budden, Ghostface, Method man....and many more....And some kind of unknown cats like Blind Fury.....Its alot of great rappers out there man...But Em, Biggie,& Pac r my top 3.
Rick you're a fucking remedial. Eminem has FIFTY THREE singles in the list of top 100 songs of all time, that fact itself proves he is number one
And no I am willing to listen to other artists. What I was trying to say is nobody else's songs are as enjoyable to me.
If yall have never had the pleasure of hearing Blind Fury check him out on Youtube...He is a blind white dude..He's amazing

Em is the GOAT! It is what it is!! He earned that label and proved it time n time again!!
